g.text: Conducted by the party who called the witness
To elicit evidence regarding facts in issue
Conducted by the party who did not call the witness
To elicit new information (establish party's own case)
To weaken, qualify, or destroy evidence given by the other party's witness
To test the reliability and credibility of the other party's witness
Conducted by the party who called the witness
To clear up ambiguity or confusion arising from cross-examination
Conducted by the party who did not call the witness
To clear up ambiguity or confusion arising from re-examination
